Test Case ID: TC-TEST6-007

Title: Verify product listing page loads efficiently under normal catalog conditions

Priority: Medium

Type: Non-Functional - Performance

Preconditions:

- Product catalog service is operational.
- Test environment monitoring tools are available.
- Network conditions are set to standard baseline for application testing.
- Catalog contains up to 50 available products.

Test Data:

- Product Set: 50 products marked Available
- Performance Threshold: Initial product listing page load completes within 3 seconds

Test Steps:

1. Start performance measurement tooling.
2. Launch the storefront application.
3. Navigate to the product listing page.
4. Measure the time from user request submission until the product list is visibly rendered and usable.
5. Repeat the measurement three times under the same conditions.
6. Record observed response times.

Expected Result:

- The product listing page loads within the defined acceptable threshold of 3 seconds under normal conditions.
- The product list is rendered completely and is usable after load.
- No timeout, partial load, or significant rendering delay occurs.
- The result supports the requirement for an efficient browsing flow.

